      • getDataAtTime

        public abstract TimestampedData getDataAtTime​(long timestamp)
                                       throws TimestampOutOfBoundsException
        Description copied from interface: HistoricalBase
        gets the TimestampedData with unix timestamp equal to unixTimestamp.
        If the unixTimestamp is in between two unix timestamps then the latter TimestampedData is returned.

        Note: this method expects the unixTimestamp parameter to be in GMT time zone
        Specified by:
        getDataAtTime in interface HistoricalBase
        Parameters:
        timestamp - - unix timestamp of TimestampedData to get
        Returns:
        TimestampedData with unix timestamp equal to or greater than unixTimestamp
        Throws:
        TimestampOutOfBoundsException
        See Also:
        TimestampedData
